  "prompt": "How can I get rid of a stink bug smell?",
  "response": "To get rid of a stink bug smell, try these methods:\n\n1. Ventilation\n- Open windows and doors\n- Use fans to circulate air\n- Run air conditioning or air purifiers\n\n2. Cleaning methods\n- Wash affected surfaces with soap and water\n- Use white vinegar solution\n- Clean with baking soda paste\n- Use hydrogen peroxide\n- Wipe surfaces with rubbing alcohol\n\n3. Odor neutralizing techniques\n- Sprinkle baking soda on affected areas\n- Use activated charcoal\n- Place coffee grounds nearby\n- Use odor-absorbing products like Febreze\n- Use essential oils like lavender or peppermint\n\n4. Preventive measures\n- Seal entry points to prevent future stink bug invasions\n- Use bug screens on windows and doors\n- Remove stink bugs carefully without crushing them\n\n5. For clothing or fabrics\n- Wash items in hot water\n- Use vinegar in the wash cycle\n- Air out clothing outside\n\n6. Natural remedies\n- Use citrus-based cleaners\n- Mix lemon juice with water\n- Use apple cider vinegar\n\nRemember that the smell can be persistent, so you might need to try multiple methods.",
